    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.03433.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
           
            <ab>Oct. 31, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. Hamilton Fish,</ab>
            <ab>Secretary of State.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your letter of the 30th instant, enclosing therein the receipted account of James P. Newcomb, Esq. for $101, for expenses incurred in obtaining the deposition of Capt. James Speed; and to inform you that a draft for the amount thereof has been sent by this day's mail to Mr. Newcomb, of Austin, Texas.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully,</ab>
            <ab>A. J. Falls,</ab>
            <ab>Chief Clerk.</ab>
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">J. P. Newcomb's acc't. $101 paid</note>
            
            
            
